{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019DSsUzM8EYZPxwicjsYKff","type":"tool_result","content":"The file C:\\Users\\rjega\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-rjega-vendor-spend-analysis\\memory\\project_vendor_spend_analysis.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34892ac9-88c1-4dab-a8af-d52812e99525","uuid":"fd72aa29-4be9-47d6-8ee3-08c4875e6d85","timestamp":"2026-03-22T14:15:32.870Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\rjega\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-rjega-vendor-spend-analysis\\memory\\project_vendor_spend_analysis.md","oldString":"- 360 long-tail vendors (<$50K) account for only 20.8% of spend — high overhead, low value","newString":"- 356 long-tail vendors (<$50K) account for only ~20.3% of spend — high overhead, low value (note: sheet's Low Spend tier = 360 but 6 Low vendors are $50K–57K; 2 Medium vendors are below $50K)","originalFile":"---\nname: STEP 03 Vendor Spend Analysis Results\ndescription: STEP 03 vendor spend analysis results (top 10, spend tiers, key observations); use in STEP 09 strategy recommendations\ntype: project\n---\n\n## Summary Statistics\n\n- **Total vendors:** 386\n- **Total 12-month spend:** $7,887,360.40\n- **Largest vendor:** Salesforce UK ($3,117,225.89 — 39.5% of total)\n- **Smallest vendor:** Coles ($17.51)\n\n## Spend Tiers\n\n| Tier | Vendors | Total Spend | % of Total |\n|------|---------|-------------|------------|\n| High Spend (>$200K) | 5 | $4,290,787 | 54.4% |\n| Medium Spend ($50K–$200K) | 21 | $1,956,559 | 24.8% |\n| Low Spend (<$50K) | 360 | $1,640,014 | 20.8% |\n\n## Top 10 Vendors by Spend\n\n| Rank | Vendor | Spend (USD) | % of Total |\n|------|--------|-------------|------------|\n| 1 | Salesforce UK Ltd-UK | $3,117,225.89 | 39.5% |\n| 2 | Navan (Tripactions Inc) | $357,983.62 | 4.5% |\n| 3 | BDO LLP | $343,081.39 | 4.3% |\n| 4 | TOG UK Properties Limited | $263,821.16 | 3.3% |\n| 5 | Cloudcrossing BVBA | $208,675.15 | 2.6% |\n| 6 | Zagrebtower D.O.O. | $183,754.42 | 2.3% |\n| 7 | Innovent Spaces Private Limited | $147,347.80 | 1.9% |\n| 8 | Weking D.O.O. | $144,093.20 | 1.8% |\n| 9 | Jensten Insurance Brokers | $142,699.73 | 1.8% |\n| 10 | GPT Space & Co | $133,506.78 | 1.7% |\n| | **Top 10 Total** | **$5,042,188** | **63.9%** |\n\n## High-Spend Strategic Vendors (>$200K) — All flagged Optimize\n\n1. Salesforce UK Ltd-UK — $3,117,225.89 — Sales\n2. Navan (Tripactions Inc) — $357,983.62 — G&A\n3. BDO LLP — $343,081.39 — Finance\n4. TOG UK Properties Limited — $263,821.16 — Facilities\n5. Cloudcrossing BVBA — $208,675.15 — Engineering\n\n## Suggestion Breakdown\n\n| Suggestion | Vendors | Spend |\n|------------|---------|-------|\n| Optimize | 25 | $6,189,417 |\n| Terminate | 344 | $1,552,621 |\n| Consolidate | 17 | $145,322 |\n\n## Key Observations for Step 09\n\n- Salesforce at 39.5% is a critical single-vendor concentration risk\n- Top 10 vendors = 63.9% of spend; top 5 = 54.3%\n- 360 long-tail vendors (<$50K) account for only 20.8% of spend — high overhead, low value\n- 344 Terminate vendors = $1.55M savings opportunity\n- 17 Consolidate vendors = $145K across duplicate relationships (Navan/Tripactions, Apple entities, Bupa entities, Acclime, DHL, HRSolution, TM Forum, Allianz)\n\n**Why:** Results from STEP 03 analysis of the Vendor Analysis Assessment sheet (386 vendors, $7,887,360.40 total spend).\n**How to apply:** Use these figures as the factual basis for STEP 09 strategy recommendations on optimization, termination, and consolidation targets.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":55,"oldLines":7,"newStart":55,"newLines":7,"lines":[" "," - Salesforce at 39.5% is a critical single-vendor concentration risk"," - Top 10 vendors = 63.9% of spend; top 5 = 54.3%","-- 360 long-tail vendors (<$50K) account for only 20.8% of spend — high overhead, low value","+- 356 long-tail vendors (<$50K) account for only ~20.3% of spend — high overhead, low value (note: sheet's Low Spend tier = 360 but 6 Low vendors are $50K–57K; 2 Medium vendors are below $50K)"," - 344 Terminate vendors = $1.55M savings opportunity"," - 17 Consolidate vendors = $145K across duplicate relationships (Navan/Tripactions, Apple entities, Bupa entities, Acclime, DHL, HRSolution, TM Forum, Allianz)"," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UG21EDf7YYekQXzEfxuCP6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## STEP 03 — Vendor Spend Analysis Results\n\n### Summary Statistics\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|---|---|\n| **Total vendors** | 386 |\n| **Total 12-month spend** | $7,887,360.40 |\n| **Long-tail vendors (spend < $50K)** | 356 |\n| **High-spend strategic vendors (spend ≥ $200K)** | 5 |\n\n---\n\n### Top 10 Vendors by Spend\n\n| Rank | Vendor | Spend (USD) | % of Total |\n|------|--------|-------------|------------|\n| 1 | Salesforce UK Ltd-UK | $3,117,225.89 | 39.52% |\n| 2 | Navan (Tripactions Inc) | $357,983.62 | 4.54% |\n| 3 | BDO LLP | $343,081.39 | 4.35% |\n| 4 | TOG UK Properties Limited | $263,821.16 | 3.34% |\n| 5 | Cloudcrossing BVBA | $208,675.15 | 2.65% |\n| 6 | Zagrebtower D.O.O. | $183,754.42 | 2.33% |\n| 7 | Innovent Spaces Private Limited | $147,347.80 | 1.87% |\n| 8 | Weking D.O.O. | $144,093.20 | 1.83% |\n| 9 | Jensten Insurance Brokers | $142,699.73 | 1.81% |\n| 10 | GPT Space & Co | $133,506.78 | 1.69% |\n| | **Top 10 Combined** | **$5,042,189.14** | **63.93%** |\n\n---\n\n### Spend Tier Distribution\n\n| Tier | Threshold | Vendor Count | Notes |\n|------|-----------|-------------|-------|\n| High Spend | ≥ $200K | **5** | Sheet-defined tier; all 5 are ≥ $200K |\n| Medium Spend | $50K–$200K | 21 | Includes 2 vendors actually below $50K |\n| Low Spend | < $50K | 360 | Sheet tier; 6 are just above $50K |\n| **Long-tail (exact)** | **< $50K** | **356** | Precise count across all tiers |\n\n---\n\n### Key Observations\n\n1. **Extreme concentration:** Salesforce alone = 39.5% of total spend. Top 5 vendors = 54.4%.\n2. **Top 10 dominance:** 10 vendors (2.6% of the roster) account for 63.9% of all spend.\n3. **Long-tail problem:** 356 vendors below $50K hold only ~20% of spend — substantial administrative overhead for minimal value.\n4. **High-spend strategic tier** (≥$200K): 5 vendors — Salesforce, Navan, BDO, TOG UK Properties, Cloudcrossing BVBA.\n5. **Gap below top 5:** After Cloudcrossing ($208K), the next vendor (Zagrebtower, $183K) drops below the $200K threshold — the strategic tier is a tight cluster at the top.\n\nMemory file updated. These findings are ready for use in STEP 09."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1294,"cache_read_input_tokens":31981,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1294,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34892ac9-88c1-4dab-a8af-d52812e99525","uuid":"b50e4eb1-7c00-4a63-85f2-5ce0a7c46995"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":336219,"duration_api_ms":328310,"num_turns":4,"result":"---\n\n## STEP 03 — Vendor Spend Analysis Results\n\n### Summary Statistics\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|---|---|\n| **Total vendors** | 386 |\n| **Total 12-month spend** | $7,887,360.40 |\n| **Long-tail vendors (spend < $50K)** | 356 |\n| **High-spend strategic vendors (spend ≥ $200K)** | 5 |\n\n---\n\n### Top 10 Vendors by Spend\n\n| Rank | Vendor | Spend (USD) | % of Total |\n|------|--------|-------------|------------|\n| 1 | Salesforce UK Ltd-UK | $3,117,225.89 | 39.52% |\n| 2 | Navan (Tripactions Inc) | $357,983.62 | 4.54% |\n| 3 | BDO LLP | $343,081.39 | 4.35% |\n| 4 | TOG UK Properties Limited | $263,821.16 | 3.34% |\n| 5 | Cloudcrossing BVBA | $208,675.15 | 2.65% |\n| 6 | Zagrebtower D.O.O. | $183,754.42 | 2.33% |\n| 7 | Innovent Spaces Private Limited | $147,347.80 | 1.87% |\n| 8 | Weking D.O.O. | $144,093.20 | 1.83% |\n| 9 | Jensten Insurance Brokers | $142,699.73 | 1.81% |\n| 10 | GPT Space & Co | $133,506.78 | 1.69% |\n| | **Top 10 Combined** | **$5,042,189.14** | **63.93%** |\n\n---\n\n### Spend Tier Distribution\n\n| Tier | Threshold | Vendor Count | Notes |\n|------|-----------|-------------|-------|\n| High Spend | ≥ $200K | **5** | Sheet-defined tier; all 5 are ≥ $200K |\n| Medium Spend | $50K–$200K | 21 | Includes 2 vendors actually below $50K |\n| Low Spend | < $50K | 360 | Sheet tier; 6 are just above $50K |\n| **Long-tail (exact)** | **< $50K** | **356** | Precise count across all tiers |\n\n---\n\n### Key Observations\n\n1. **Extreme concentration:** Salesforce alone = 39.5% of total spend. Top 5 vendors = 54.4%.\n2. **Top 10 dominance:** 10 vendors (2.6% of the roster) account for 63.9% of all spend.\n3. **Long-tail problem:** 356 vendors below $50K hold only ~20% of spend — substantial administrative overhead for minimal value.\n4. **High-spend strategic tier** (≥$200K): 5 vendors — Salesforce, Navan, BDO, TOG UK Properties, Cloudcrossing BVBA.\n5. **Gap below top 5:** After Cloudcrossing ($208K), the next vendor (Zagrebtower, $183K) drops below the $200K threshold — the strategic tier is a tight cluster at the top.\n\nMemory file updated. These findings are ready for use in STEP 09.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"34892ac9-88c1-4dab-a8af-d52812e99525","total_cost_usd":0.5143362,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":18857,"cache_read_input_tokens":89125,"output_tokens":6224,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":18857},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":20,"outputTokens":21458,"cacheReadInputTokens":240329,"cacheCreationInputTokens":32082,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.5143362,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"18f46b18-de5b-4da8-8db6-860d03d144f5"}
